fields.name: Monstera
fields.description: Monstera is a tropical plant that is known for its large, glossy leaves with unique splits and holes. It is a popular choice for indoor gardening and can grow quite large, making it a stunning focal point in any room.

fields.name: African violet
fields.description: African violet is a popular houseplant known for its beautiful, velvety leaves and vibrant purple flowers. It thrives in moderate light and requires regular watering to keep the soil moist but not soggy.

fields.name: Aloe Vera
fields.description: Aloe Vera is a succulent plant known for its medicinal properties and ability to thrive in dry conditions. It has thick, fleshy leaves that store water, making it a low-maintenance houseplant.

fields.name: Anthurium
fields.description: Anthurium is a tropical plant known for its striking, heart-shaped flowers and glossy leaves. It is often used as a decorative houseplant and can bloom year-round with proper care.

fields.name: Areca Palm
fields.description: Areca Palm is a popular indoor palm known for its feathery, arching fronds. It is a great air purifier and can grow quite tall, making it an excellent choice for larger spaces.

fields.name: Begonia
fields.description: Begonia is a diverse genus of plants known for their colorful foliage and unique leaf shapes. They are often grown as houseplants and can thrive in various light conditions.

fields.name: Phalenopsis Orchid
fields.description: Phalenopsis Orchid, also known as the moth orchid, is a popular houseplant known for its long-lasting flowers and elegant appearance. It thrives in bright, indirect light and requires regular watering.

fields.name: Christmas Cactus
fields.description: Christmas Cactus is a popular holiday plant known for its vibrant flowers that bloom during the winter months. It is a low-maintenance houseplant that prefers bright, indirect light and moderate watering.
